## Monitoring and Logging

### Structured Logging

All webhook processing includes:
- `traceId`: Request correlation ID
- `sepayId`: SePay transaction ID
- `transactionId`: Internal transaction ID
- `processingTime`: Webhook processing duration

### Key Metrics

- Webhook processing time
- Duplicate detection rate
- Authentication failure rate
- Transaction success rate

## Item Purchases and Entitlements (NEW)

Items can be obtained via multiple sources and must integrate with the payment system:

- points_purchase: User buys points (via SePay) and spends points to unlock items
- cash: Direct cash purchases (optional future flow)
- vip_sub: Items granted as part of an active VIP subscription
- redeem_code / giftcode: Items redeemed via gift codes

### Flow 3: Item Purchase via Points (example)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Frontend
    participant Backend
    participant MongoDB

    User->>Frontend: Select item and confirm purchase (points)
    Frontend->>Backend: POST /api/v1/payments/convert-points or dedicated endpoint
    Backend->>MongoDB: Check user.points >= price
    alt Enough points
        Backend->>MongoDB: Deduct points; add item to users.items and item_sources[item_id] = "points_purchase"
        Backend-->>Frontend: { success: true, items }
    else Not enough points
        Backend-->>Frontend: { success: false, error: "INSUFFICIENT_POINTS" }
    end
```

### VIP Entitlements Behavior
- Items with source = vip_sub are active only while VIP is active.
- On VIP expiry: mark such items inactive (do not remove history); re-activate upon VIP renewal.

